    <id>http://jdodds.github.io/blog/2015/01/01/what-makes-a-codebase-good</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>A <a href="https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=8818159">recent discussion on hacker news</a> got me thinking about what makes a good codebase. After thinking about it for a while, I&rsquo;ve come up with the following rule of thumb:</p>

<p>A good codebase is one that both <strong>does what it is expected to do</strong> and <strong>doesn&rsquo;t fill it&rsquo;s maintainers with negative emotions</strong>.</p>
